# Section Contrast Rules

Prevent dark/light mode regressions. See `AGENTS.md` → **Section Contrast Rules** for the full flow.

## 1. Never hardcode text colors

Forbidden on `color` / copy:

- `#0f172a`, `#111827`, `#ffffff`, `#f8fafc`

Use:

- `var(--live-section-fg)` — light section paint
- `var(--live-section-muted)`
- `var(--live-section-fg-on-dark)` — **only** inside dark-painted column/card/stack

## 2. Dark surface rule

Dark painted column/card/stack (`#0a0a0a`, navy band, etc.):

- Set `data-dark-surface="true"` **or** call `applyTemplateSectionContrast()` in `lib/getInTouchSection.js`
- Copy: `var(--live-section-fg-on-dark)` — **never** `var(--live-section-fg)` on nested dark cards (inherits light row `#0f172a`)

## 3. Section tone rule

Resolve `data-section-tone="light"|"dark"` via `resolveSectionToneForNode()` + `applySectionToneToLeafCss()` in `lib/sectionToneContext.js`. Do not sweep entire light rows with descendant tone CSS.

## 4. New template rule

Before merge, test:

- Light site preset + Dark site preset
- Mixed page (light section + dark card inside)
- Builder canvas, draft preview, published live (same `liveRenderer` / `buildBuilderLiveRenderOptions` pipeline)

## 5. Theme tokens

Prefer `--token-text-primary`, `--token-text-muted`, `--token-bg-primary`, `--token-bg-surface`, `--token-border-default`. No new hardcoded slate neutrals in shared/live/template CSS.

## 6. Builder/live parity

Contrast fixes must work in builder canvas, draft preview, and published live. No builder-only CSS hacks.

## 7. Regression tests

New template → extend `tests/sectionToneContext.test.mjs`, `tests/darkSurfaceContext.test.mjs`, `tests/mixedContrastContext.test.mjs`, `tests/getInTouchSection.test.mjs`.

## 8. Audit

Run `npm run audit:section-contrast` before merge. Fix banned neutrals on `color:` in audited CSS paths.
